defaultForgdefaulting the Links – Rape investigation and prosecution (2012)default2.4 In this report (which was conducted jointly with HM Inspectorate of the Crown Prosecution Service), HMIC found that there were wide variations across forces in the number of rapes that remained on the system (and so were investigated) compared to those
default that were ‘no crimed’ (i.e. removed from the crime recording system because the police decide that a crime has not been committed). We 
defaultstated
